node.text: Omg y’all.....add this to the list of crazy things we used to do before Rona! This was exactly 1 year ago and little did I know I was documenting the very last time I went out grocery shopping with both kids 😂😂 Let’s just say I didn’t need a pandemic to tell me not to do that again!

node.text:
So I got up this morning to get the kids ready and realized I forgot to buy milk last night 😱 Then I remembered the instant porridges that the lovely team at @gracefoods gave to me and I thought well they can eat this! It was their first time trying it and they loved it! You know I always make porridge for them so if they liked this, then it must be really good! Definitely adding this to my list of quick breakfasts for those school mornings when I’m short on time! .

node.text:
There’s a lot of misinformation circulating around regarding Jamaica’s lockdown protocols! Don’t cancel your travel plans, I promise you, Jamaica is a safe place to visit. I’d recommend that you travel Tuesday to Saturday or Wednesday to Monday. Get the most out of those days when you’re free to do as you please and trust me, if a non movement day falls on your last day you’re going to be wiped out from all the activities you’re going to want to stay on your resort to relax anyway! Lastly, always make sure to follow @visitjamaica and go to visitjamaica.com to complete your travel authorization and get all the info you need. @andrewholnessjm ‘s twitter account also gives live updates on when the non-movement days are occuring as well.
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
Maaannn back when I was playing mas with my friends nobody could tell me nothing 😂 Labor Day Weekend was somebody’s backyard bashment on Saturday night, and partying in Temptations until 8AM on Monday. My best friend’s mom was Guyanese and she’d have cookup rice, baked mac n cheese, chow mein, and chicken ready for us to chow down before we put our costumes on and headed out to meet our band on Eastern Parkway! This nice pot of pelau takes me back! Team dry pelau all the way! Check out the recipe on my YouTube channel: Thatnursecancook and subscribe while you’re there! 
.
.
.
.
.
.

node.text: Cantonese Lobster from Catch LA. This was yummy. I typically don’t eat whole lobsters but this was good. Good enough for 2. Reservations are hard to get though. First time I came here I made the reservation a month in advance. Second time, I made it 3 weeks in advance got the last spot for the day. Some say it may all be hype but the quality of the food backs it up!

node.text: How do y’all feel about donuts? We’ve been back from LA for a few days now and I’m still thinking about these donuts 😫 I’m not even a donut person but Randy’s got it! I had 1 glazed donut and it was such a sweet treat! #donuts #losangeles #randysdonuts

node.text: You guys are amazing 🎊🎉 It’s been an incredible journey thus far and I’m thankful for the opportunity to be welcomed into your homes to share my love of cooking with you all. Life has been crazy these past few months and as I’m preparing my transition away from bedside nursing, I can only imagine what else God has in store for me. I’m not chasing material things, I’m chasing the freedom to live life on my own terms. Thank you thank you all so much for the support and encouragement! Up next? My hardcover cookbook! Sooner than you think! 🤎

node.text:
Coconut milk in the tin: I have about 5 at any given time stocked in my pantry. But have you ever had someone make you rice & peas with freshly made coconut milk? That’s love right there🤎 I choose the right coconut by shaking it and holding it to my ear. If you can hear the juice inside swishing back and forth then it’s a good one! Use a hammer to loosen the shell, use your hand or sometimes a knife to loosen the meat from the shell, chop it up, and blend it with water. Not too much water though! It’ll be too watery! I remove as much water as I can from the peas when it’s done cooking and set it aside. Then add in the coconut milk. You should yield about 2 cups of coconut milk. Boil the peas in coconut milk and a cup of that water you set aside from the peas & then add rice! Voila! Rice name shelly! 😂 I used parboiled rice this time. There’s a tutorial on my YouTube channel that goes deeper into detail so make sure you subscribe! Type in the search: thatnursecancook rice and peas if you have trouble finding it! 
.
.
.
.
.
